## 10. External Tool Evaluation

When the user points you at an external tool, follow this flow: (1) Read docs thoroughly, (2) Map against existing skills (duplicate/complementary/new), (3) Prefer delegation section in existing skill, (4) Only create new skill for major standalone systems (24+ commands). See `references/tool-integration-pattern.md` for the full evaluation flow, integration patterns, and pitfall: over-integration.

## 11. Retired Capability Cleanup

When a capability is retired: (1) `grep -r "old-name"` across all skill dirs, (2) Classify each reference (prose → replace, section → remove, data values → leave, audit logs → leave), (3) Rename support files, (4) Update support file maps, (5) Rename cache keys in `.skills_prompt_snapshot.json`, (6) Re-grep to confirm zero remaining references (excluding `.archive/` and audit logs).

